<div id="review_2381824145" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2381824145" />
    <a title="Daniel" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/80955006-daniel"><img alt="Daniel" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1529969584p2/80955006.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2381824145?book_show_action=true">Apr 23, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Daniel" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Daniel" href="/user/show/80955006-daniel">Daniel</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/80955006-daniel?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2381824145" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5066646201714434949"><strong>After thirty years</strong><br/><br/>My goodness. Some thirty odd years ago I read this for the first time. Reread this today and it was every bit as good today, perhaps even better. I understand the craft of writing a bit better now, and can say that Anne was a true master storyteller. All ages and lovers of good stories will appreciate this story of wonderful Menolly and her journey towards Harper Hall.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


